{"metadata":{"title":"Apple Push Certificate","modules":[{"name":"BrazeKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Braze\/tutorials\/Braze\/b1-standard-push-notifications"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation","title":"Related Documentation"},{"title":"Push Notifications","anchor":"Push-Notifications","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Braze\/tutorials\/Braze\/b1-standard-push-notifications","doc:\/\/Braze\/tutorials\/Braze\/b2-rich-push-notifications","doc:\/\/Braze\/tutorials\/Braze\/b3-push-stories","doc:\/\/Braze\/tutorials\/Braze\/b4-live-activities"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Create an Apple Push file or certificate.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/Braze\/apns-certificate","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before you can send a push notification using Braze, you must provide your Push notification file or certificate from Apple. You may present either a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p8"},{"type":"text","text":" file (recommended) or a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"text":" certificate.","type":"text"}]},{"text":".p8 File (recommended)","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"p8-File-recommended"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As described on this ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/help.apple.com\/developer-account\/#\/devcdfbb56a3","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In your developer account, go to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/ios\/certificate"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Under Keys, select All and click the Add button (+) in the upper-right corner.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Under Key Description, enter a unique name for the signing key.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Under Key Services, select the APNs checkbox, then click Continue. Click "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirm"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note the Key ID. Click ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Download","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to generate and download the key now."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you download the key, it is saved as a text file with a .p8 file extension. Save the file in a secure place because the key is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not saved in your developer account and you won’t be able to download it again"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigate to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/dashboard-01.braze.com\/app_settings\/app_settings"},{"type":"text","text":" page in the dashboard and upload the .p8 file."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When prompted, also enter your app’s ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/ios\/identifier\/bundle\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/ios\/authkey"},{"text":" that you noted when generating the key, and your ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/#\/membership","isActive":true},{"text":". Click ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Save","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":3,"anchor":"p12-Certificate-legacy","type":"heading","text":".p12 Certificate (legacy)"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you may utilize Apple’s older authentication scheme ("},{"code":".p12","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" SSL certificates). Unlike the ","type":"text"},{"code":".p8","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" solution described above, these certificates automatically expire every year and will require you to regenerate and re-upload them. Braze will send you email reminders as the certificate approaches expiration to help your notifications continue uninterrupted, but because this is a manual process we recommend utilizing the above-described ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p8"},{"text":" authentication scheme instead. However, if you still wish to, you may configure and upload ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"text":" certificates as described here:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Step 1: Generate Certificate Signing Request","anchor":"Step-1-Generate-Certificate-Signing-Request"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Navigate to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/ios\/manage\/overview\/index.action"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Select "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Identifiers"}]},{"text":" in the left sidebar and filter ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"App Ids","type":"text"}]},{"text":" using the button on the right of the page ","type":"text"},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-identifiers-app-ids.png"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Select your application."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enable push notifications by checking the checkbox then click "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Edit","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-app-id-config.png"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Click Create Certificate under the Production SSL Certificate ","type":"text"},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-modal.png"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Production SSL Certificate","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are suitable for App Store and TestFlight builds. Use a "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Development SSL Certificate"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" to for development builds."}]}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Follow the instructions from the SSL certificate assistant."}]}]}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You must update your provisioning profile for the app after you create your SSL certificates. A simple “Refresh” in the organizer will accomplish this.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"anchor":"Step-2-Export-Certificate","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Step 2: Export Certificate"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Download the production push certificate that you just created and open it with the Keychain Access application.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In Keychain Access, click on My Certificates and locate your push certificate.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Export it as a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"type":"text","text":" file and use a temporary, unsecure password (you will need this password when uploading your certificate to Braze)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Navigate to the ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitle":"Settings","identifier":"https:\/\/dashboard-01.braze.com\/app_settings\/app_settings","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Settings","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" page in the dashboard and upload your production certificate. "},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-upload.png"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can upload either your development or production push certificates to the dashboard for your distribution provisioning profile apps, but you can only have one active at a time. As such, if you wish to do repeated testing of push notifications once your app goes live in the App Store, we recommend setting up a separate App Group or App for the development version of your app."}]}]}]}],"references":{"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit":{"abstract":[{"text":"The main Braze framework providing user sessions, attributes and events logging, push notification support.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/brazekit","title":"BrazeKit","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit"},"doc://Braze/tutorials/Braze/b3-push-stories":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/tutorials\/Braze\/b3-push-stories","role":"project","estimatedTime":"20min","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to support receiving "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/www.braze.com\/docs\/user_guide\/message_building_by_channel\/push\/advanced_push_options\/push_stories\/","type":"reference"},{"type":"text",